{
  "texts": [
    "Or rather, what kind of imitation?",
    "The behavior to be imitated, implicitly assumed as intelligent, is linguistic-the only domain Turing identifies as potentially impervious to counterfeiting when conducted correctly.",
    "The criterion for correctness is that of interactive linguistic conversation, open to any topic.",
    "Such proficiency symbolizes intelligence due to the infinitely productive and nuanced nature of language from a semantic standpoint.",
    "Essentially, one cannot feign fluency in a language convincingly."
  ]
}